  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Restore the hope of 1000 refugee women and girls</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Restore my hope will provide Group and Individual Trauma counseling services to 1,000 conflict affected refugee women and children living in Adjumani Refugee settlement of Uganda. Adjumani settlement currently hosts over 240,000 refugees, 65% being women and children below the age of 18 years. 60% of the women and girls living at Adjumani have either been raped, tortured or lost loved one, leaving them extremely traumatized. This project will improve on their mental and physical health.</narrative>
  </description>
